{
  "title": [
    "midi.in"
  ],
  "description": "get cooked MIDI data",
  "origin": "ELSE",
  "categories": [
    "MIDI"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "raw MIDI data"
        },
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "MIDI channel"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "anything",
          "description": "Cooked MIDI data"
        },
        {
          "type": "float",
          "description": "MIDI channel"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "MIDI channel (0 is OMNI)",
      "default": "0"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [],
  "methods": [],
  "body": "[midi.in] sends \"cooked\" MIDI data instead of \"raw\" data like [midiin] with MIDI data type symbol, values and channel (but a note output is sent as a simple numeric list). It can take a raw MIDI input via its inlet but it also listens to your connected MIDI device."
}